Package minesweeper.game.states

Enum CellState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CellState>
      • minesweeper.game.states.CellState

  • public enum CellState
extends java.lang.Enum<CellState>
    Enum class to indicate the public state of a cell. The information stored in CellState[][] states should be free to access because it is the public interface of the board through which the player perceives the game.

      • TEMP_UNC0

        public static final CellState TEMP_UNC0
        A temporary CellState when cannot auto uncovered some cells. In mousePressed event callback, the board will temporarily set those cells to UNC0 blank state and mark them in the 2D array as TEMP_UNC0. Later in mouseRelease callback, the board will redraw their look and set their states back to COVERED again.

        public static boolean isUncovered​(CellState state)
